# Meridian CRM — POS Integration Knowledge Base

## POS System Registry

Meridian supports 80+ POS systems across 5 verticals:
- **Restaurant**: Toast, Square, Clover, Lightspeed Restaurant, SpotOn, Revel, TouchBistro, Aloha (NCR), MICROS (Oracle), Heartland, Lavu, CAKE, Aldelo, Focus POS, Digital Dining, Future POS, PixelPoint, Brink, Simphony, Qu POS, SkyTab, Rezku, Upserve, Talech, Loyverse, Gloria Food, Olo
- **Retail**: Square, Clover, Shopify POS, Lightspeed Retail, Stripe Terminal, PayPal Zettle, SumUp, KORONA POS, Hike POS, Rain POS, NCR Voyix, Bindo POS, Erply, AccuPOS, RetailEdge, PHP POS, Cashier Live, WooPOS, Openbravo
- **Automotive**: Tekmetric, Shop-Ware, Mitchell1 Manager SE, ShopMonkey, AutoFluent, Shop Boss, R.O. Writer, Protractor.NET, ALLDATA Manage, Omnique, AutoVitals, NAPA TRACS, TireMaster, Bolt On Technology
- **Coffee/Cafe**: Square, Toast, Clover, TouchBistro, Loyverse, KORONA POS, Rezku
- **Smoke Shop/Cannabis**: Square, Clover, Shopify POS, Lightspeed Retail, POS Nation, Cova POS, Treez, Flowhub, Dutchie POS, Meadow, Blaze, BioTrack, LeafLogix, IndicaOnline, KORONA POS, Bindo POS, Cashier Live

## Integration Tiers

| Tier | Count | Status | Data Flow |
|------|-------|--------|-----------|
| 1 | 3 | Integrated | Real-time OAuth2 + webhooks |
| 2 | 13 | Coming Soon | API available, integration in progress |
| 3 | 22 | Contingency | CSV/Excel manual import or third-party bridge |
| 4 | 13 | Unsupported | Contact us, partner API required |
| 5 | 9 | International/Niche | Regional or specialized systems |

## Integration Statuses

- `integrated` — Full native integration via OAuth2. Real-time data flow. Square, Toast, Clover.
- `coming_soon` — API documented, integration being built. Tekmetric, Shop-Ware, ShopMonkey, Lightspeed, SpotOn, Revel, Heartland, Qu POS, SkyTab, Upserve, Dutchie POS.
- `contingency` — Manual CSV/Excel upload or third-party bridge (Zapier, Make.com). Data flows but not real-time.
- `unsupported` — Enterprise/partner API required. Contact team for custom pipeline.

## Sales Rep POS Workflow

When a sales rep creates a new customer via the Create Customer form:

1. **Business Details** — Rep enters business info and selects the customer's POS system from the searchable dropdown
2. **Select Plan** — Rep chooses pricing tier (US: $500/$750/$1000, Canada: $339/$675/$1350 CAD)
3. **Confirm & Provision** — System shows the selected POS alongside business details for confirmation
4. **Account Ready** — Customer portal is provisioned; POS system is stored in org metadata

The POSSelectorPanel component shows:
- **Layout A** (integrated): One-click OAuth connect button with step-by-step instructions
- **Layout B** (contingency): CSV export instructions + Zapier bridge option + waitlist signup
- **Layout C** (coming_soon/unsupported): Estimated timeline, manual import option, email waitlist

## POS Data Model

Each POS system entry includes:
- `key` — Unique identifier (kebab-case)
- `status` — integrated | coming_soon | contingency | unsupported
- `tier` — 1-5 priority level
- `verticals` — Array of supported business types: restaurant, fast_food, coffee, retail, auto_shop, smoke_shop
- `integrationStatus` — API availability, OAuth, webhooks, sandbox, effort level
- `contingencyPlan` — Workaround, export format, instructions, limitations
- `connectionRequirements` — Credentials, permissions, hardware, plan, step-by-step
- `dataAvailable` — What data types are accessible (sales, inventory, employees, customers, menuItems, realTime, historicalDays)

## Common POS Credential Patterns

| Auth Type | Systems | Pattern |
|-----------|---------|---------|
| OAuth2 | Square, Toast, Clover, Lightspeed, SpotOn, Shop-Ware, Treez, Dutchie | Redirect flow, merchant approves permissions |
| API Key | Tekmetric, ShopMonkey, Revel, KORONA, Erply, Cova, Flowhub | Key generated in POS admin settings |
| Partner API | Aloha, MICROS, Brink, Simphony, Xenial, NCR Voyix, Olo | Requires formal partnership agreement |
| No API | Mitchell1, Focus POS, Digital Dining, Future POS, Harbortouch, R.O. Writer | Manual CSV/Excel export only |

## Rate Limits (Key Systems)

| System | Rate Limit | Notes |
|--------|-----------|-------|
| Square | 1000/min | Per OAuth token |
| Toast | 100/sec | Per restaurant GUID |
| Clover | 16/sec | Per merchant |
| Lightspeed | 1/sec (leaky bucket) | Drip rate per account |
| Shopify | 2/sec (leaky bucket) | REST API; GraphQL has cost-based limits |
| Stripe | 100/sec | Per API key |

## Vertical-Specific Notes

### Restaurant
- Primary POS: Toast (dominant in US full-service), Square (popular with independents)
- Key data: covers/table turns, menu items, labor, tips
- Look for: PAYMENTS_READ, ORDERS_READ, ITEMS_READ, EMPLOYEES_READ permissions

### Automotive
- Primary POS: Tekmetric and Shop-Ware (modern cloud); Mitchell1 (legacy dominant)
- Key data: repair orders (R.O.s), parts inventory, bay utilization, customer vehicles
- `menuItems` is always false — auto shops don't have menus
- Look for: service history, vehicle data, parts lookup

### Smoke Shop / Cannabis
- Primary POS: Dutchie (dominant after Green Bits acquisition), Cova, Flowhub
- Compliance tracking is critical — seed-to-sale, age verification, purchase limits
- Key data: product categories (flower, edibles, concentrates, accessories), compliance reports
- Cannabis POS systems typically have the richest inventory data

### Coffee
- Most use generic POS (Square, Toast, Clover) rather than coffee-specific systems
- Key data: morning rush patterns, drink customizations, loyalty/regular customer tracking
- Look for: hourly distribution data (heavy morning peak 7-9 AM)

### Retail
- Wide variety of POS systems from free (Square, Loyverse) to enterprise (NCR Voyix)
- Key data: inventory turns, product mix, seasonal patterns, customer segments
- Shopify POS users may have both online and in-store data to merge

